T> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>4:56:08 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/beeryeyed?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">New to the board, but I do have FLASH question...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I've got to say I've been to a number of digital art boards, but this one really targets my interests in digital coloring and Manga/Anime style.  Anywho, I was wondering if anyone here knew anything about using Flash 5 swf files as a windows wallpaper on the desktop?  </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uswordsmanjubei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swordsman Jubei</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://cgull.gamehappy.com/10x10.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Member</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>2/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>5:57:31 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://cgull.gamehappy.com/captainfuturebbs.jpg width=69 height=100></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: New to the board, but I do have FLASH question...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Uh hmm...I'm guessing here, cause I don't have windows 98 or higher on this PC, but you might be able to do it using Active Desktop in win98 or higher.  The actual SWF file you can't really use unless you put it in a website or make it an exe.  The thing would be, if you were to use it on your active desktop, this is - if you can - and it's an animation, it would probably play the flash movie over and over again as your desktop, which would seem to be rather annoying after a while.  It might also hog up a bunch of system resources.<br>
If you just want one single frame, I suggest you pause it and take a screenshot of it (Print Screen button on your keyboard - then open an imaging program and hit paste), and make that your wallpaper.<br>
I hope that helped,<br>
